  "name": "Ghastly Cauldron",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>This black cooking pot can produce a feast fit for undead.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Activate</strong> <span class=\"action-glyph\">3</span> Interact</p>\n<p><strong>Frequency</strong> once per day</p>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong> The cauldron must be filled with water, herbs, bones, and raw meat, and kept at a boil for 1 hour</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> As you stir the cauldron, its contents transform into 10 meals suitable for undead consumption. Each meal must be ladled from the cauldron individually as a 3-action activity and must be eaten within 1 hour of removal. An undead creature that consumes a meal from the cauldron regains [[/r 5d8[healing]]]{5d8 Hit Points} and gains the benefits of 4th-level <em>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.SnaLVgxZ9ryUFmUr]{Restoration}</em> that you choose; living creatures who consume a meal from the cauldron take @Damage[5d8[void]] damage (@Check[type:fortitude|dc:27|basic:true]) instead. Any meals remaining in the cauldron 24 hours after activation become inedible slurry.</p>"
    },
